{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/Neovim/20-live-server/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"b12d027e-6997-52aa-97c5-cb5cc19fbaa3","html":"<h2>What is Live Server?</h2>\n<p>Live-server is an <code class=\"language-text\">npm</code> package that will allow you to see real time changes for <code class=\"language-text\">.html</code> files in your browser.</p>\n<h3>Note</h3>\n<p>You will need to have <code class=\"language-text\">node</code> &#x26; <code class=\"language-text\">npm</code> installed I have a blog post about installing node using <code class=\"language-text\">fnm</code> <a href=\"https://www.chrisatmachine.com/Nodejs/02-Install-FNM/\">here</a></p>\n<h2>Install</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      npm i -g live-server\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Commands</h2>\n<p>You can have live server monitor and html file like this:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      live-server some-file.html\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>Or watch a directory like this:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      live-server some-directory/\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  ","excerpt":"What is Live Server? Live-server is an  package that will allow you to see real time changes for  files in your browser. Note You will need‚Ä¶","frontmatter":{"title":"Using Live Server with Neovim","tags":["neovim"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/a8734/neovim.png"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":3.456140350877193,"src":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/5134e/neovim.png","srcSet":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/06f82/neovim.png 197w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/da7d7/neovim.png 393w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/5134e/neovim.png 786w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/31987